/* Every enum constant is always implicitly public static final. Since it is static, 
we can access it by using the enum Name. Since it is final, we canâ€™t create child enums.
We can declare the main() method inside the enum.
Hence we can invoke enum directly from the Command Prompt.
*/

// A Java program to demonstrate that we can have main() inside enum class.

enum Color 
{
  RED,
  GREEN,
  BLUE;
  public static void main(String[] args)
  {
    Color c1 = Color.RED;
    System.out.println(c1);
  }
}
